Cybersecurity Threat Landscape (Part 3 - Verizon)
In this part, you should primarily use the Verizon Data Breaches Investigation Report plus independent research to answer the below questions.

What is the difference between an incident and a breach?
Incident is an event where the integrity, confidentiality or availability of information is compromised
Breach is a confirmed exposure of data to unauthorized parties
What percentage of breaches were perpetrated by outside actors? What percentage were perpetrated by internal actors? 
Outside actors - 69%
Internal actors - 34%
What percentage of breaches were perpetrated by organized criminal groups? 
39%

What percentage of breaches were financially motivated? 
71%

Define the following: 

Denial of Service: An attack designed to overwhelm networks and systems to compromise availability. 

Command and Control: Malware that allows that attack to communicate and/or control an infected system.

Backdoor: Malware that once on a system allows attackers to bypass normal authentication to access a system. 

Keylogger: A spyware type or malware that is used to record keystrokes and sent back to the persons operating the program.

The time from an attackerâ€™s first action to the initial compromise of an asset is typically measured in which one? Seconds, minutes, hours, days? 
Minutes

When it comes to phishing, which industry has the highest click rates?
Education
